{"id":191,"parent_id":190,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":191,"title":"Revelation 1: The Revelation of Jesus Christ","subtitle":"","short_title":"Revelation 1: The Revelation of Jesus Christ","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-1-the-revelation-of-jesus-christ","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-1-the-revelation-of-jesus-christ"},[".heading",{"id":"head2","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-1-the-revelation-of-jesus-christ.head2"},["h1","Revelation 1"],[".subtitle","The Revelation of Jesus Christ"],[".intro","The island of Patmos was mainly a Roman prison camp. Christians were greatly persecuted during the last part of the first century. John himself was banished to the Isle of Patmos for the word of God and for the testimony of Jesus Christ (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1.9"},"Revelation 1:9"],"). Even in those circumstances, however, John sought the Spirit “on the Lord’s day” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1.10"},"Revelation 1:10"],") and had a marvelous vision of Jesus Christ, which we read about in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1"},"Revelation 1"],"."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-1-the-revelation-of-jesus-christ.f2"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1"},"Revelation 1"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Signified it"],"(v. 1)"],["td","Revealed or delivered it"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","First begotten of the dead"],"(v. 5)"],["td","First to be resurrected"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Dominion"],"(v. 6)"],["td","Authority, rule, to rule over"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Alpha and Omega"],"(vv. 8, 11)"],["td","The first and last letters of the Greek alphabet; name title of the Savior"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Tribulation"],"(v. 9)"],["td","Trials and troubles"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","The Lord’s day"],"(v. 10)"],["td","The Christian Sabbath (Sunday), the day of the week the Lord was resurrected"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Girt about the paps"],"(v. 13)"],["td","Wrapped around the chest"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","His countenance"],"(v. 16)"],["td","Appearance, especially the expression on the face"],["td"]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-1-the-revelation-of-jesus-christ.p29"},"Do activities A and B as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1"},"Revelation 1"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"A Revelation of Jesus Christ"],[".figure",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-1-the-revelation-of-jesus-christ.f3"},["p.preamble","In your notebook, list what you learn about Jesus Christ from",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1"},"Revelation 1"],"."],["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Answer one of the following two questions: What did you learn about Jesus Christ in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1"},"Revelation 1"],"that you did not know about Him before? What most impressed you about Jesus Christ as you read what John wrote about Him?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Why do you think it is important to know these things about Jesus as you begin reading Revelation?"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"Interpreting Important Symbols"],["p.para",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-1-the-revelation-of-jesus-christ.p32"},"Find the following symbols in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1"},"Revelation 1"],"and write what you think each symbol represents and what it teaches us. In the Joseph Smith Translation for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1"},"Revelation 1"],"and in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1.20"},"Revelation 1:20"],"the Lord explained the meaning of some of the symbols that John saw. (You may want to read again “Look for Types and Symbolic Meanings,” p. 5, for help with interpreting symbols.)"],["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","Seven golden candlesticks (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1.12-13,20"},"Revelation 1:12–13, 20"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/18.24"},"3 Nephi 18:24"],")"]],["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","The white appearance of the Savior (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1.14"},"Revelation 1:14"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/alma/13.24"},"Alma 13:24"],")"]],["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","Seven stars in the right hand of the Savior (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1.16,20"},"Revelation 1:16, 20"],"; see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/jst/jst-rev/1.1-8,20"},"JST, Revelation 1:1–8, 20"],"and note the change in the word",["span.emphasis","angels"],")"]],["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","The Savior’s tongue is compared to a two-edged sword (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1.16"},"Revelation 1:16"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/hel/3.29"},"Helaman 3:29"],")"]],["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","The face of the Savior glowing like the sun (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1.16"},"Revelation 1:16"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.7"},"D&C 88:7"],")"]]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
